Do you need help during COVID-19 from the City of San Antonio? Are you worried about housing, paying bills, childcare, food, doctor visits or other city services? See a full list of city services available in the attached flyer.

You can also get the latest information from the City of San Antonio COVID-19 hotline with a new segment presenting the most relevant topics. The helpline is available Monday to Friday from 8:00 a.m. to 7:00 p. m., and Saturdays and Sundays from 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Call 210-207-5779 or you can also email your questions to covid-19@sanantonio.gov.

post_text: Did you know the first #EarthDay was founded in 1970 by Senator Nelson from Wisconsin! This movement has raised environmental activism to another level. Millions of people gather around this day to figure out new solutions to protect the planet from pollution, toxic dumps and the extinction of wildlife. For fun Earth Day activities for kids please visit https://littlebinsforlittlehands.com/hands-on-earth-day-activities-for-kids/. #ScienceFacts #FunFacts

post_text: All our teachers and administrators work hard as we continue to grow and provide distance learning. These are our #HarlandaleChronicles
shared_text:
Rayburn_HISD
April 6 at 5:27 PM ·

Rayburn academic dean, Mrs. Toscano, and principal, Dr. Santos, wake up early every Monday morning ready to start their “home” work, too. They’ve created a comfortable work space, make a list of things to do for the day, and take brain breaks in between. Eating a healthy snack and walking outside for fresh air is also a part of their work routine. You should try their strategies! It keeps them smiling... you will smile too!
